The paper discusses modeling and analysis of interactions among services, which falls under the domain of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses formal models and verification techniques, which are related to Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Lastly, the paper focuses on the realizability and conformance of choreographies, which is related to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
